  "short_text": "Celsius to Fahrenheit",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a temperature in Celsius and converts it to Fahrenheit. Use shorthand if-else to label the result as `Cold` if the Fahrenheit temperature is below 50°F; otherwise, print `Warm`.\n\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nUse the formula `F = C * 9/5 + 32` for the conversion from Celsius to Fahrenheit.\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n#### Input\n\nA line containing a single integer representing the Celsius temperature.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output is a single word: `Cold` or `Warm`.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the input is:\n\n```\n10\n```\n\nThe output should be:\n\n```\nWarm\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "e47c3c06-d94f-4491-bf13-bb9f024acac8",
      "code_content": "celsius = int(input())\nfahrenheit = celsius * 9/5 + 32\nprint(\"Cold\" if fahrenheit < 50 else \"Warm\")",
